&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full time/ part time/ job share&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Located in Aberystwyth in mid West Wales, Bronglais General Hospital is one of the smallest acute DGH’s in the UK however this does not stop us from being forward thinking. We have consultant advanced radiographers roles in place.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As well as PACS the Radiology department has 3 general rooms (1 located within the A&amp;E dept), a multi slice CT scanner, a Mammo unit, dental room, 3 ultrasound units and a digital screening room. We have the only open MRI scanner in the Welsh NHS. Further supported by mobile units for theatre and ward work.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We have a very attractive on-call system (On-site and from home) that provides competitive remuneration and WTD compliant rest time, participation in which would be expected.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews for this post will be held on 25th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameMark SherrattJob titleLead RadiographerEmail addressmark.sherratt@wales.nhs.ukTelephone number01970 635683&lt;/p&gt;
